Format: https://www.debian.org/doc/packaging-manuals/copyright-format/1.0/
Upstream-Name: yojimbo
Upstream-Contact: Glenn Fiedler <glenn@mas-bandwidth.com>
Source: https://github.com/mas-bandwidth/yojimbo
Comment: The netcode/, reliable/, serialize/ and sodium/ directories are
 vendored copies of their own upstream projects, present so that source
 builds have zero dependencies. The Debian package is built with
 -DYOJIMBO_SYSTEM_DEPS=ON, so none of them are compiled into the binary
 package — the libserialize-dev, libreliable-dev, libnetcode-dev and
 libsodium-dev packages are used instead. tlsf/ IS compiled into the
 library: it is a private implementation detail of yojimbo's per-client
 allocators, not a public dependency. For the official Debian archive the
 unused vendored directories should additionally be stripped from the
 orig tarball via Files-Excluded (see DEBIAN.md in the packaging
 repository).

